Odd ANDERSEN / AFP JOHANNESBURG - The country’s freight industry is reeling from the flooding in KwaZulu-Natal.  The country’s freight industry is reeling from the flooding in KwaZulu-Natal. Roads around the Durban port are unusable, with operations still suspended at terminals. #DStv403 #SouthAfricanTonight pic.twitter.com/f8ztkerSQA  Roads around the Durban port are unusable with operations still suspended at terminals. READ: IN PICS: Floods wreak havoc in KZN The world’s biggest container line Maersk has told eNCA that most of its containers seen washed away in video footage were empty at the time. It says while it is aware of some looting incidents there has been no impact on customer cargo. The Road Freight Association says it’s in the process of retrieving containers and vehicles washed away at depot sites around eThekwini. But it says port access is the biggest concern.